The paper describes the use of machine learning techniques, specifically integrable deep neural networks, for representing high-dimensional free energy functions in material systems. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and could also be classified under sub-categories such as modeling and simulation (cs.MS), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), systems and control (cs.SY), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
